.DT
lpick
$MUDNAME$ Command Help
lpick

.SH lpick - Used to pick locks
.SI 5
.EI

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
lpick <object> with <object>
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5
When you encounter a locked door, lpick is the command you need to use.

To successfully pick a locked door, you need to have a lockpick and must be
holding it.  Then you can attempt to pick the lock, with the difficulty
based on a number of factors, including your skill, the difficulty of the
lock, and the light level of the room.
.EP

.SH Example
.SI 5
>lpick door with lockpick
You begin to examine the lock on the south door, trying to find out as
much as you can about it.
You insert the lockpick into the lock.
You start to sweat as you continue to work on the lock.
You jiggle the lockpick, and the lock pops open!

>lpick door with lockpick
You begin to examine the lock on the south door, trying to find out as
much as you can about it.
You insert the lockpick into the lock.
You start to sweat as you continue to work on the lock.
Try as you might, you fail to make the lock open.
.EI

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
.EP
